Knecht, collector in Zürich, Seebacher Strasse 171, telephoned from Zürich to inquire about the picture N°1 (Sailing Ships & Burning Town) in the earlier editions of my Bruegel paintings, which I have withdrawn from the 3rd edition. column4: <content>Shortly before midday a Hr. Knecht, collector in Zürich, Seebacher Strasse 171, telephoned from Zürich to inquire about the picture N°1 (Sailing Ships & Burning Town) in the earlier editions of my Bruegel paintings, which I have withdrawn from the 3rd edition. It was offered to him by a German dealer whose name he was not permitted to disclose. I told him that I have withdrawn the picture from the 3rd edition because after recent study of the original in London, I no longer believed in Bruegel's authorship. I asked him not to tell the dealer that he had spoken to me which he promised (as this was also in his interest). He did not give me the price asked, saying that this was being negotiated.</content>
<object.title>Landscape with Sailing Boats and a Burning Town</object.title>
